METHODS: A total of 359 gastric cancer patients who underwent curative surgery 
between March 2011 and March 2015 were enrolled; 80 of these patients (22.2%) 
were octogenarians and older. Surgical approaches included MIS (50 laparoscopic 
and 65 robotic) and open surgery (n = 244). Surgical outcomes of MIS and open 
